The paper discusses a vision-based system for robotics and self-driving cars, which falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO). The paper also focuses on simultaneous localization and mapping (SLAM), which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The paper proposes improvements to a state-of-the-art SLAM system, which involves machine learning techniques (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper evaluates the performance of the proposed system, which involves system analysis and control (cs.SY).
